    "Then, we will evaluate our trained model on three external MedVQA benchmarks, VQA-RAD 16, SLAKE 17 and ImageClef-VQA-2019 18.",
    "Note that, our model has two variants, which are tailored to encoder-based and decoder-based language models, respectively, denoted as MedVInT-TE and MedVInT-TD.",
    "At last, we establish a generative MedVQA benchmark with PMC-VQA, and evaluate various pre-trained visual or language models using our framework, serving as a reference to promote future research in generative medical VQA.",
